The paper deals with signal processing and optimization problems related to recovering frequencies and amplitudes from undersampled observations. This suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in imaging, radar, and localization, which could fall under the sub-categories of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper uses convex optimization techniques, which could place it in the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
